            code: `Claim: Coin is biased toward heads (p > 0.5)

Step 1 — State hypotheses:
  H₀: p = 0.5 (fair coin)
  H₁: p > 0.5 (biased toward heads)

Step 2 — Choose α = 0.05

Step 3 — Collect data: 100 flips, 60 heads

Step 4 — Compute test statistic (z-test for proportion):
  z = (p̂ - p₀) / √(p₀(1-p₀)/n)
    = (0.60 - 0.50) / √(0.5×0.5/100)
    = 0.10 / 0.05 = 2.0

Step 5 — Decision:
  p-value = P(Z > 2.0) = 0.0228
  0.0228 < 0.05 → Reject H₀
  Conclusion: Evidence suggests the coin is biased.`,
