            title: 'Example: One-sample Z-test for mean',
            code: `Population: μ₀ = 100, σ = 15 (known)
Sample: n = 36, x̄ = 105
Test: Is the sample from this population?

Step 1 — Hypotheses:
  H₀: μ = 100
  H₁: μ ≠ 100 (two-tailed)

Step 2 — α = 0.05, critical Z = ±1.96

Step 3 — Compute Z-statistic:
  Z = (x̄ - μ₀) / (σ/√n)
    = (105 - 100) / (15/6)
    = 5 / 2.5 = 2.0

Step 4 — p-value = 2 × P(Z > 2.0)
         = 2 × 0.0228 = 0.0456

Step 5 — Decision:
  |2.0| > 1.96 and p = 0.0456 < 0.05
  → Reject H₀`,
