            code: `Group A (new drug): n₁ = 25, x̄₁ = 82, s₁ = 10
Group B (placebo):  n₂ = 25, x̄₂ = 75, s₂ = 12
Test: Does the drug improve scores?

Step 1 — Hypotheses:
  H₀: μ₁ = μ₂
  H₁: μ₁ > μ₂ (one-tailed)

Step 2 — α = 0.05, df = 25 + 25 - 2 = 48

Step 3 — Pooled variance:
  s²p = [(24×100) + (24×144)] / 48
      = [2400 + 3456] / 48 = 121.17

Step 4 — Standard error:
  SE = √(121.17 × (1/25 + 1/25))
     = √(121.17 × 0.08) = √9.69 ≈ 3.11

Step 5 — t-statistic:
  t = (82 - 75) / 3.11 = 7 / 3.11 ≈ 2.25

Step 6 — Critical t(48, 0.05) ≈ 1.677
  2.25 > 1.677 → Reject H₀`,
