            title: 'Example: Mann-Whitney U Test',
            code: `Group A scores: [12, 15, 18, 22, 25]
Group B scores: [10, 14, 20, 24, 30]

Step 1 — Combine and rank all values:
  10(B)=1, 12(A)=2, 14(B)=3, 15(A)=4,
  18(A)=5, 20(B)=6, 22(A)=7, 24(B)=8,
  25(A)=9, 30(B)=10

Step 2 — Sum ranks for each group:
  RA = 2+4+5+7+9 = 27
  RB = 1+3+6+8+10 = 28

Step 3 — Compute U statistics:
  UA = nA×nB + nA(nA+1)/2 - RA
     = 5×5 + 5(6)/2 - 27
     = 25 + 15 - 27 = 13

  UB = nA×nB - UA = 25 - 13 = 12

Step 4 — Compare to critical value:
  U = min(UA, UB) = 12
  Critical U(5,5, 0.05, two-tailed) = 2
  12 > 2 → Fail to reject H₀`,
