          text: 'Think of a symphony. You hear melody (trend), a repeating riff (seasonality), long swells and fades (cycles), and the hiss of the hall (noise). A time series is the same: four overlapping parts sum to what you observe. Curiosity gap: why does separating these parts make forecasting easier? Because each part obeys different rules and is modelled by a different method.',
