          content: [
            `<p>EDA for time series is the systematic use of plots and summary stats to uncover the data's structure. A line plot shows trend and obvious seasonality; a seasonal plot (one curve per year) shows whether seasonality is stable or evolving; lag plots and ACF reveal memory; rolling mean/variance reveal non-stationarity.</p>`,
            '<p>ACF (autocorrelation function) shows total correlation at lag k; PACF (partial) removes intermediate lags to show direct correlation. Together they identify AR vs MA structure: a PACF cutoff after lag p suggests AR(p); an ACF cutoff after lag q suggests MA(q).</p>',
            '<p>Always EDA <em>before</em> modelling because the plots dictate the model family. A series with a trend and ACF decaying slowly needs differencing; one with a sharp seasonal lag in ACF needs seasonal terms. Skipping EDA is the most common cause of model misspecification.</p>'
          ]
