          text: `Think of looking at a mountain through a heat haze. The jagged peaks shimmer, but if you blur your eyes the mountain's true shape emerges. A moving average does exactly that: it replaces each point with the average of a window of nearby points, blurring noise to reveal the underlying trend. Curiosity gap: why does a bigger window make the curve <em>smoother but laggier</em>? Because each estimate includes older, less-relevant points.`,
