          heading: 'What is Simple Exponential Smoothing?',
          text: `Think of how you form an impression of a friend's mood. You weight today's behaviour most heavily, yesterday a bit less, last week less still — a fading memory. Simple Exponential Smoothing (SES) does the same for a series: it forecasts the next value as a weighted average of all past observations, with weights that decay geometrically. Curiosity gap: how can an <em>infinite</em> weighted average be computed in one line using only the last forecast? Through a clever recursion.`,
