            title: 'Weak stationarity conditions + AR(1) example',
            code: `Weak (covariance) stationarity requires:
  (1) E[Y(t)] = mu              for all t
  (2) Var(Y(t)) = sigma^2       for all t
  (3) Cov(Y(t), Y(t+k)) = gamma_k   depends only on k, not t

AR(1): Y(t) = phi*Y(t-1) + e(t), e~WN(0,sigma_e^2)
  Mean:     E[Y] = 0  (if |phi|<1)
  Variance: Var(Y) = sigma_e^2 / (1-phi^2)   (constant if |phi|<1)
  ACF:      rho_k = phi^k                    (depends only on k)
  => AR(1) is stationary IFF |phi| < 1.
  If phi = 1 -> unit root -> random walk -> NON-stationary.

Worked example: phi=0.7, sigma_e^2=1
  Var(Y) = 1/(1-0.49) = 1.96
  rho_1 = 0.7, rho_2 = 0.49, rho_5 = 0.168

Python:
  import numpy as np
  phi=0.7; se2=1.0
  print("Var:", round(se2/(1-phi**2),3))
  print("ACF:", [round(phi**k,3) for k in range(1,6)])`,
