          heading: 'What is an ARMA Process?',
          text: `Think of your mood today as a mix of two things: momentum from yesterday's mood (autoregression) plus today's random events (moving average of shocks). ARMA models exactly this: today's value is a combination of its own past values plus a weighted sum of recent shocks. Curiosity gap: AR and MA look different — when are they actually the same model in disguise? When an AR process is "invertible", it can be rewritten as an infinite MA, and vice versa — they are two lenses on the same DGP.`,
