          text: 'Think of a song with two rhythms at once: a fast beat (weekly) and a slow chorus (yearly). Plain ARIMA hears only the fast beat; SARIMA hears both. It adds seasonal AR and MA terms that operate at lag s, so the model can capture patterns repeating every 12 months, 7 days, or 24 hours. Curiosity gap: how can one model contain <em>two</em> ARIMA models — one at lag 1 and one at lag s — without exploding in parameters? Because the seasonal polynomials are sparse: they act only at multiples of s.',
